{
  "info": {
    "name": "matchX API — Contrato completo",
    "description": "Colección generada desde los handlers MSW y services del frontend matchX.\n\nCada request refleja exactamente la estructura que el frontend envía y espera recibir.\n\n## Convenciones\n- **Base URL**: variable `{{base_url}}`\n- **Auth**: Bearer token en variable `{{token}}` (se setea automáticamente con el request 'Login directo')\n- **Wrapper de respuesta**: `{ data: ..., status: 'ok' }`\n- **Error shape**: `{ message, errors: { _general: [...] } }`\n\n## Ver también\n- docs/API_ENDPOINTS.md — documentación exhaustiva\n- docs/DATABASE_GAPS.md — tablas/campos nuevos por crear",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://35.243.241.205:8082",
      "description": "URL base del backend"
    },
    {
      "key": "token",
      "value": "",
      "description": "JWT obtenido del login. El request 'Login directo' lo setea automáticamente."
    }
  ],
  "auth": {
    "type": "bearer",
    "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{token}}", "type": "string" }]
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "description": "Login, logout y usuario actual",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login directo",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (body.token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('token', body.token);",
                  "    console.log('Token guardado en {{token}}');",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"ana@matchx.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
            },
            "description": "Login con credenciales. Response: { token, user }.\nSi credenciales inválidas → HTTP 422.\nSi usuario tiene múltiples roles → { status: 'select_profile', profiles: [] }."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Login con selectedRole",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "auth": { "type": "noauth" },
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "login"] },
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"username\": \"carlos@matchx.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password\",\n  \"selectedRole\": \"superadmin\"\n}"
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Logout",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/logout", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "logout"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "User actual (opcional)",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/user", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "user"] },
            "description": "NO mockeado por MSW. Si el backend lo implementa, debe devolver el mismo objeto user del login."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
